This paper deals with the application of reinforcement learning in humanoid robots to learn coordinated tasks in cluttered environments. The paper focuses on motion planning and collision avoidance, which are key areas of research in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The proposed framework is based on multi-task reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves object recognition and manipulation, which can be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with real-time planning and control, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
